indicators.justification:
According to the Close Corporation Act 26 of 1988, section 3, the standard for beneficial ownership of a business are 
(a) the full name;
(b) previous names, if any;
(c) the nationality;
(d) national identity number or passport number; or
(e) date of birth; and
(f) contact particulars.

Internally, BIPA has information systems that shows the changes of hands/shareholding/ownership of the organisation over time.

However such information is only available as structured open data for internal purposes within BIPA.
